macro.title: The U.S. Housing Market Is Stuck, With Sales and Listings Barely Budging
macro.what: Home sales and new listings were little changed from a month and a year earlier in October, and prices have also shown signs of flattening
macro.why: Price trend signals wealth effects and buyer/seller power.
macro.market: Firm prices help builder margins; softness hits comps and sentiment.

macro.title: Redfin Economists’ Weekly Take: Lack of Fresh Economic Data May Prevent December Rate Cut
macro.what: This Week In A Nutshell With the government open, mortgage rates may wobble as we digest the September jobs report this Thursday and hear from the statistical agencies about what fresh data will be arriving before the December 10 Fed meeting
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

housing.title: October’s Most Expensive Home Sales Include Adam Levine’s Former Montecito Compound
housing.what: California and Florida dominated October’s ultra-luxury housing market, with oceanfront estates and celebrity homes going for more than $30 million
housing.why: Inventory and velocity drive pricing power and volume.
housing.market: Rising inventory/DOM tilts to buyers; tight supply supports prices.

housing.title: How a 50-Year Mortgage Would Differ From a 30-Year Mortgage—and What It Would Mean for Homebuyers
housing.what: A proposed 50-year mortgage could lower monthly payments, but buyers would pay far more interest over time and build equity far more slowly
housing.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
housing.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

housing.title: Redfin Debuts Conversational Search to Reinvent How You Find Homes
housing.what: The AI feature allows you to have a back-and-forth dialogue with Redfin while you search, helping you discover homes that best suit your preferences For years, online real estate search has been limited by filters and map boundaries
housing.why: Relevant development for housing and markets.
housing.market: Watch second-order effects across builders, lenders, and REITs.
